Job Description

We are searching for a passionate Machine Learning engineer/ software developer to join our Data Science team.

Qualifications

Main Duties & Responsibilities:

Design, build and maintain applications, pipelines and workflows for our data science use-cases;
Work closely with data scientists to bring prototype ML models to production;
Work with other teams to provide data and build cloud infrastructure for our ML solutions;
Take part in ML model maintenance, retraining and quality monitoring;
Work with business and technical stakeholders to select and design data science solutions;
Continuous learning about state-of-the-art technologies and practices in the data science and engineering domain.

Qualifications:

University degree in numerical field (Computer science, Machine Learning, Mathematics, Physics, Engineering, etc.);
Experience as software developer with at least one of the languages: Python, Scala, Java;
Experience with SQL and Big data processing frameworks such as Spark or Flink;
Experience with at least one ML framework and knowledge in at least one Machine Learning field such as regression, classification, clustering, optimisation, statistics.
Experience bringing a machine learning solution to production;
Experience with AWS or other cloud provider;
Highly proficient in spoken and written English;
Excellent communication skills and a pragmatic approach to problem-solving;
Willingness to learn and interest in the latest trends in programming and machine learning.

Nice to Have:

Experience with MLOps;
Knowledge of Scala and interest in functional programming highly appreciated;
Experience with Kafka, Clickhouse, Postgres, Kubernetes, Docker.

