You And Your Team

You will join the team of around 40 colleagues based in Gdynia. Altogether your major responsibility will be to monitor market events related to legal entity data, build company’s profile and business descriptions & hierarchy relation trees and assign company classification codes.

You will be much exposed to partner with several internal teams located around the world, which makes this job diverse and gives opportunity to learn constantly. You will also be a partner for our customers supporting them to use our products.

WHY IS THIS JOB IMPORTANT?

The information which you provide is immediately displayed in our ﬂagship products: Datascope Select and Eikon. Our customers, mostly international banks and risk managers take advantage of your expertise to take their business decisions every day.

Compensation

You will receive the annual gross salary of 60 000 PLN. You will also be entitled to a language bonus scheme and additional benefits that we offer to Refinitiv colleagues.

What Do You Need To Bring

Proficient English and Spanish or Balkan languages;
Practical knowledge of MS Excel on intermediate level;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
Eagerness to learn a lot and collaborate with others;
Strive for bringing the best customer service;

You Will Be Even More Competitive If

You know more than one foreign language;
You have validated research skills
You have got intermediate VBA and/or SQL skills;
You have a master’s degree in Economics/Finance or equivalent experience;
You have knowledge and curiosity about legal entity structure;
You are familiar with our flagship products: Eikon and Datascope;
You have knowledge about market regulations related to the legal entities.

Some Of Daily Tasks You Will Perform

Maintain legal entities profiles in a database
Perform research on local sources (e.g. registries, regulators, stock exchanges, annual reports)
Monitor and update market events;
Build ownership structure of a company in the database;
Complete profile creations requests in a timely manner;
Classify companies based on global regulatory framework or international industrial classifications;
Perform quality control checks to ensure data accuracy;
Respond to client’s queries, explaining methodology.

At LSEG, we believe that creating a diverse and inclusive organisation is fundamental to the way we deliver on our promise of creating essential partnerships and open opportunities. Our open culture is central to how we deliver our purpose – driving financial stability, empowering economies and enabling customers to create sustainable growth – in everything we do.

Working with us means that you will be part of a dynamic organisation of 25,000 people across 70 countries. However, we will value your individuality and enable you to bring your true self to work so you can help enrich our diverse workforce. You will be part of a collaborative and creative culture where we encourage new ideas and are committed to sustainability across our global business. You will experience the critical role we have in helping to re-engineer the financial ecosystem to support and drive sustainable economic growth. Together, we are aiming to achieve this growth by accelerating the just transition to net zero, enabling growth of the green economy and creating inclusive economic opportunity.

LSEG offers a range of tailored benefits and support, including healthcare, retirement planning, paid volunteering days and wellbeing initiatives.

